  "prompt": "Why is New York Mets pitcher Matt Harvey called \"The Dark Knight\"? Did the team and MLB get permission from DC Comics for his Batman-themed merchandise?",
  "response": "Matt Harvey, a pitcher for the New York Mets, earned the nickname \"The Dark Knight\" due to his dominant performances on the mound and his association with the character of Batman, who is often referred to by the same name. The nickname reflects Harvey's intense demeanor and high level of skill, which drew comparisons to the iconic superhero. \n\nAs for the merchandise, while there was significant Batman-themed branding associated with Harvey during his time with the Mets, the team and MLB did not officially seek permission from DC Comics for the use of the \"Dark Knight\" nickname or related merchandise. This led to some controversy, as it blurred the lines of intellectual property rights. Ultimately, while the nickname became widely recognized among fans and the media, it was a product of Harvey's performance and persona rather than a licensed trademark from DC Comics.",
